%U A394943 27666351665,92408318931,309370042571,1037954086435,3489342871382,11752086858742,39649541430122,133987563425658
%N A394943 Number of well-formed bracketed words of total length n built from the symbol * (of length 1) and three unary bracket types (), [], and {}, with no empty bracket pair, where every maximal chain of unary brackets is written in canonical weakly increasing order.
%C A394943 a(0)=1 counts the empty word.
%C A394943 For n>=1, a(n)=b_{3,1}^c(n) in the notation of Au and Bremner; see Section 3.
%C A394943 Equivalently, a(n) counts canonical representatives of such bracketed words under commutativity of the three unary bracket types.
%C A394943 In each maximal chain of nested unary brackets, the bracket types are weakly increasing from outermost to innermost.
%C A394943 Equivalently, a(n) counts rooted ordered trees in which each leaf represents *, each unary internal node is labeled 1, 2, or 3, every non-unary internal node has at least 2 ordered children, and the labels along every maximal unary chain are weakly increasing from the root toward the leaves.
%C A394943 Equivalently, a(n) counts peakless Motzkin paths of length n with three types of up-steps U_1, U_2, U_3, such that along every matched ascent the labels are weakly increasing.
%C A394943 Here a matched ascent is a maximal consecutive block of up-steps whose matching down-steps all belong to the same descent.
%H A394943 Yu Hin Au and Murray R. Bremner, <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2604.25731">Enumerating Multi-Operator Monomials in Commutative and Noncommutative Settings</a>, arXiv:2604.25731 [math.CO], 2026. See pp. 4, 19 (Table 4).
%F A394943 G.f.: 1 + (1 - x - 3*x^2 + 3*x^4 - x^6 - sqrt((1-x-3*x^2+3*x^4-x^6)^2 - 4*x*(3*x^2 - 3*x^4 + x^6))) / (2*(3*x^2 - 3*x^4 + x^6)) = 1 + A(x).
%F A394943 G.f. satisfies A(x) = x + x*A(x) + (3*x^2 - 3*x^4 + x^6)*(A(x) + A(x)^2).
%F A394943 a(n) = f(n-1) + 3*f(n-2) - 3*f(n-4) + f(n-6) + 3*Sum_{k=1..n-3} a(k)*a(n-2-k) - 3*Sum_{k=1..n-5} a(k)*a(n-4-k) + Sum_{k=1..n-7} a(k)*a(n-6-k) with a(0)=a(1)=1 where f(n)=a(n) for n>=1 and f(n)=0 for n<=0.
%e A394943 a(5)=25 = 1 + 18 + 6: one word with no unary operators, namely *****; 18 words with one unary operator, namely P_i(**)*, *P_i(**), P_i(***), P_i(*)**, *P_i(*)*, **P_i(*) for i=1,2,3; and 6 canonical double-unary words P_i(P_j(*)) with 1<=i<=j<=3.
%Y A394943 Cf. A004148, A394942, A394944, A394940.
